│   │
│   ├── 📄 GlobalDnsNotificationBar.tsx
│   │   Purpose: Displays a persistent notification bar at the top of the screen if DNS records are not fully verified.
│   │   Details:
│   │     - Consumes `DnsStatusContext` to get `overallDnsStatus`, `dnsContextLoaded`, and `isDnsModalOpenGlobally`.
│   │     - Conditionally renders based on `overallDnsStatus` (not 'verified' or null) and `dnsContextLoaded`.
│   │     - Hidden if `isDnsModalOpenGlobally` is true.
│   │     - Color and message change based on status (pending/partial vs. failed). Yellow for pending/partially_verified, Red for failed_to_verify.
│   │     - Determines its `top` position (`top-0` or `top-16`) based on whether the current page is in `PAGES_WITHOUT_NAVBAR` (e.g., `/dashboard`, `/editor`).
│   │     - Visibility is further refined by `shouldShowBasedOnPageEligibility`: only shows on `/dns-confirmation`, pages after it in `FORM_FLOW_ORDER`, or pages not in `FORM_FLOW_ORDER` at all.
│   │     - Clicking the bar calls `showDnsModal()` from the context to open the `DnsConfigurationModal`.
│   │   Usage: Rendered globally by `src/core/App.tsx`.
│   │
│   ├── 📄 Navbar.tsx
│   │   Purpose: Navigation bar for the application, themed for the jungle look. Handles user authentication status for displaying links.
│   │   Details: Provides main site navigation links. Styled with a dark green background, white text, and yellow accents. 
│   │     - Imports `useAuth` to get `user` and `signOut` function.
│   │     - Conditionally renders a "Sign Out" button if a user is logged in. Clicking it calls `signOut()` and navigates to the homepage.
│   │     - If no user is logged in, it displays only a "Sign in" link (Sign up button removed).
│   │     - Includes responsive behavior for mobile (hamburger menu) and desktop.
│   │   Usage: Used globally across most pages.
│   │
